  "prompt": "A bag contains 4 balls. Two balls are drawn at random and are found to be white. What is the probability that all balls are white?",
  "response": "To determine the probability that all four balls in the bag are white given that two balls drawn at random are white, we'll use **Bayesian probability**.\n\n### Step 1: Define Possible Scenarios\nAssume that each ball is either **white** or **non-white**, and initially, all color combinations are equally likely. Let \\( N \\) be the number of white balls in the bag. The possible values of \\( N \\) are 2, 3, or 4 because we know that at least two white balls were drawn.\n\n### Step 2: Calculate Prior Probabilities\nThe **prior probability** \\( P(N=k) \\) of having \\( k \\) white balls in the bag is based on the number of ways to choose \\( k \\) white balls out of 4:\n- \\( P(N=2) = \\frac{\\binom{4}{2}}{2^4} = \\frac{6}{16} \\)\n- \\( P(N=3) = \\frac{\\binom{4}{3}}{2^4} = \\frac{4}{16} \\)\n- \\( P(N=4) = \\frac{\\binom{4}{4}}{2^4} = \\frac{1}{16} \\)\n\n### Step 3: Calculate Likelihoods\nThe **likelihood** \\( P(\\text{two white} | N=k) \\) is the probability of drawing two white balls given that there are \\( k \\) white balls in the bag:\n- For \\( N=2 \\): \\( P(\\text{two white} | N=2) = \\frac{\\binom{2}{2}}{\\binom{4}{2}} = \\frac{1}{6} \\)\n- For \\( N=3 \\): \\( P(\\text{two white} | N=3) = \\frac{\\binom{3}{2}}{\\binom{4}{2}} = \\frac{3}{6} = \\frac{1}{2} \\)\n- For \\( N=4 \\): \\( P(\\text{two white} | N=4) = \\frac{\\binom{4}{2}}{\\binom{4}{2}} = 1 \\)\n\n### Step 4: Apply Bayes' Theorem\nUsing Bayes' Theorem, the posterior probability \\( P(N=4 | \\text{two white}) \\) is:\n\n\\[\nP(N=4 | \\text{two white}) = \\frac{P(\\text{two white} | N=4) \\cdot P(N=4)}{\\sum_{k=2}^{4} P(\\text{two white} | N=k) \\cdot P(N=k)}\n\\]\n\nPlugging in the values:\n\n\\[\nP(N=4 | \\text{two white}) = \\frac{1 \\cdot \\frac{1}{16}}{\\left(\\frac{1}{6} \\cdot \\frac{6}{16}\\right) + \\left(\\frac{1}{2} \\cdot \\frac{4}{16}\\right) + \\left(1 \\cdot \\frac{1}{16}\\right)} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{16}}{\\frac{1}{16} + \\frac{2}{16} + \\frac{1}{16}} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{16}}{\\frac{4}{16}} = \\frac{1}{4}\n\\]\n\n### Conclusion\nThe probability that all four balls in the bag are white, given that two drawn balls are white, is **\\(\\frac{1}{4}\\)**.\n\n**Answer:**  \nThe probability is 1\u20444.",
